text:
Hey all! Home stretch! :fire::confetti_ball::coolblobrainbow:

For tonight's in-class activity, you'll be doing a project closeout. Here are the kinds of items to discuss:
• Go back and look at the requirements for your MVP
    ◦ Did your team meet the goals that they set? 
    ◦ If they didn’t what’s the plan to get the project finished?
• Look over your ReadMe for the project
    ◦ Does it easily detail the project so that folk who didn’t work on it also understand what the project is about? 
    ◦ What are ways that you can make it more clear? 
• What’s the biggest thing each team member accomplished on the project? 
• Celebrate completing your MVP!!
For anyone who needs to make-up demos or interviews, keep an eye on your slack (diligently) for your reviewing TA's message.

There is no attendance code for tonight.

I will be doing demos for a good portion of the evening, so please send me a slack message if you need anything and I'll get back to you ASAP.
